The paper deals with the effects of electromagnetic (EM) pulses on secure software running on a superscalar out-of-order microprocessor, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The proposed methodology and fault classification can also be useful for software engineering (cs.SE) and electronics and embedded systems (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of these EM pulse effects on control-flow hijacking, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
